        "subtitle": "Lesson 1 · A1",
        "body": "In this lesson you'll learn the essential French greetings and polite words you'll use every single day. Ready? Let's begin!"
      },
      "metadata": { "estimatedSeconds": 20 }
    },
    {
      "id": "c2",
      "type": "VocabularyCard",
      "content": {
        "word": "Bonjour",
        "nativeTranslation": "Bonjour",
        "englishTranslation": "Hello / Good morning",
        "pronunciation": "bon-ZHOOR",
        "ipa": "bɔ̃ʒuʁ",
        "partOfSpeech": "interjection",
        "difficulty": "easy",
        "exampleSentence": "Bonjour, comment ça va ?",
        "nativeExample": "Hello, how are you?",
        "audio": { "key": "fr/a1/bonjour.mp3" }
      },
      "metadata": { "estimatedSeconds": 30 }
    },
    {
      "id": "c3",
      "type": "VocabularyCard",
      "content": {
        "word": "Merci",
        "nativeTranslation": "Merci",
        "englishTranslation": "Thank you",
        "pronunciation": "mair-SEE",
        "ipa": "mɛʁsi",
        "partOfSpeech": "interjection",
        "difficulty": "easy",
        "exampleSentence": "Merci beaucoup !",
        "nativeExample": "Thank you very much!",
        "audio": { "key": "fr/a1/merci.mp3" }
      },
      "metadata": { "estimatedSeconds": 30 }
    },
    {
      "id": "c4",
      "type": "InfoCard",
      "title": "Formal vs. informal",
      "content": {
        "tone": "tip",
        "body": "Use \"Bonjour\" during the day and \"Bonsoir\" in the evening. \"Salut\" is casual — save it for friends, not your boss!"
      },
      "metadata": { "estimatedSeconds": 25 }
    },
    {
      "id": "c5",
      "type": "GrammarCard",
      "title": "Politeness formulas",
      "content": {
        "explanation": "French politeness often pairs a greeting with a title. Notice how \"s'il vous plaît\" (please) uses the formal \"vous\".",
        "examples": [
          { "text": "S'il vous plaît", "translation": "Please (formal)" },
          { "text": "S'il te plaît", "translation": "Please (informal)" },
          { "text": "De rien", "translation": "You're welcome" }
        ]
      },
      "metadata": { "estimatedSeconds": 35 }
    },
    {
      "id": "c6",
      "type": "FlashCard",
      "title": "Quick flip",
      "content": { "front": "Au revoir", "back": "Goodbye", "hint": "Tap to reveal the meaning" },
      "metadata": { "estimatedSeconds": 15 }
    },
